---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ & Terms"
  description="Turnaround times, revision policy, deposit terms, rush fees, file formats and usage rights for Clout & Context Animation."
>
  <section class="faq-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
        <h1>Frequently asked questions</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item" open>
          <summary>What's the turnaround time?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Standard turnaround varies by tier — visualisers and Hook Videos typically turn around faster than
            Story-Based or Premium Cinematic pieces, which involve more scenes and revisions. Your quote will
            include a specific delivery date once the storyboard is signed off. Clip packages are scheduled
            monthly once the 3-month minimum is agreed.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How many revisions do I get?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Performance Visualiser and Hook Video include <strong>one revision</strong>. Story-Based and Premium
            Cinematic include <strong>two revisions</strong>. Clip packages include one revision per clip.
            Additional revisions beyond what's included are billed at £30–75 depending on scope.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do deposits work?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Music videos and custom-quoted work are booked with a <strong>50% deposit</strong> invoiced on
            agreement, with the balance invoiced on delivery. Monthly clip packages are paid upfront each month,
            not on delivery.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What happens if I go quiet mid-project?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            We'll follow up and hold your slot for a reasonable period, but ongoing work pauses if we're waiting
            on feedback, assets or sign-off from you. If a project goes unresponsive for an extended period, the
            deposit is retained to cover the work already completed and the reserved production slot, and the
            project is closed. Get in touch any time to pick it back up.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What file formats do you deliver?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Standard delivery is H.264 MP4 at the resolution and aspect ratio agreed for the job — typically
            1080p landscape for music videos, and vertical <em>and</em> square formats for social clips so you
            can post to TikTok, Reels and Shorts from one deliverable. Other formats (ProRes, specific codecs for
            a broadcaster or platform) can be arranged on request.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What if I need it faster?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Rush delivery is available on Story-Based and Premium Cinematic music videos, and on clip packages,
            for an additional <strong>25–50%</strong> depending on how much the timeline is compressed. Hook
            Video is standard turnaround only — there's no rush option on that tier, as the scope is already
            capped to keep it fast and affordable.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you sell music videos and clips separately?</summary>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Yes — clips packages and single clips can be bought independently of a music video. But every music
            video quote can include a clips package for the release rollout, cut from the finished animation, so
            you've got promo content ready the moment the video goes live.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="terms" class="terms-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h2>Terms of Service</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-copy">
        <h3>Deposits &amp; payment</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Custom-quoted work (music videos, one-off add-ons) requires a 50% deposit before work begins, invoiced
          via Stripe. The balance is invoiced on delivery. Monthly clip packages are paid upfront at the start of
          each billing period, with a 3-month minimum commitment before switching to rolling monthly. Unused
          clips in a monthly package do not roll over to the following month.
        </p>

        <h3>Revisions</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Performance Visualiser and Hook Video include one revision; Story-Based and Premium Cinematic include
          two; clip packages include one revision per clip. Additional revisions are billed at £30–75 depending
          on complexity, agreed before work begins.
        </p>

        <h3>Deadlines &amp; rush work</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Delivery dates are agreed once a storyboard (for music videos) or brief (for clips) is signed off.
          Rush delivery, where available, carries a fee of 25–50% on top of the standard price, reflecting
          compressed scheduling.
        </p>

        <h3>Rights &amp; usage</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          The client owns the finished animation delivered to them. <strong>Clout &amp; Context retains the
          right to use the work for promotion and portfolio purposes</strong> — including the showreel, website,
          Instagram, TikTok, YouTube and pitches to prospective clients. Where a client has a specific reason to
          delay this (an unreleased track, a label embargo), a hold period can be agreed so the work is shown
          only after the release date, rather than the right being waived entirely.
        </p>

        <h3>Cancellations &amp; unresponsive projects</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          If a client becomes unresponsive for an extended period after work has started, the deposit is
          retained to cover work completed and the production slot reserved. Monthly clip packages can be
          cancelled after the 3-month minimum with notice ahead of the next billing date.
        </p>

        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Questions about these terms — <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .faq-item summary::marker {
    color: var(--c-cyan);
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .terms-section {
    background: var(--c-surface);
  }

  .terms-copy {
    max-width: 72ch;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .terms-copy h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }
</style>
